---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Methodology – True Evaluators"
  description="Research Methodology for Academic Evaluation for Foreign Equivalency. A meticulous research methodology to collect and analyze information, ensuring a credible and dependable assessment."
>

  <!-- ── HERO ── -->
  <section class="inner-hero">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>Methodology</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── DUAL IMAGES ── -->
  <section style="background:var(--clr-bg-cream);padding-bottom:clamp(2rem,4vw,3.5rem);">
    <div class="container dual-imgs">
      <img src="/Work-Experience-Evaluation/Work-Experience-1.webp" alt="Methodology" class="dual-img-main" />
      <img src="/Academic-Evaluation/Academic-Evaluation-Img-1.webp" alt="Methodology services" class="dual-img-side" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container intro-grid">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" width="10" height="10" aria-hidden="true" style="display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:4px;">
            <circle cx="7" cy="7" r="6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          </svg>
          True Evaluation
        </span>
        <h2 style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
          Research Methodology for Academic Evaluation for Foreign Equivalency
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="intro-label"><strong>Introduction</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-top:0.4rem;">
          The assessment of foreign academic credentials for equivalency is a pivotal
          undertaking, ensuring an equitable and precise evaluation for individuals
          seeking admission to educational institutions or professional licensing. This
          process demands a meticulous research methodology to collect and analyze
          information, thereby ensuring a credible and dependable assessment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── COMPARATIVE APPROACH ── -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background:var(--clr-bg-light);">
    <div class="container comp-grid">
      <img src="/home/Home-Trusted-Partner-Sec.webp" alt="Comparative Approach" class="comp-img" />
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" width="10" height="10" aria-hidden="true" style="display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:4px;">
            <circle cx="7" cy="7" r="6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          </svg>
          Research Method
        </span>
        <h2 style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Comparative Approach</h2>
        <p class="method-italic" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
          Employing this method involves a thorough comparison between the foreign
          educational system and qualifications and those of the target country.
          This encompasses:
        </p>
        <ul class="checklist" style="margin-top:1rem;">
          {[
            'Acquisition of information on the foreign education system, including curriculum, credit systems, grading scales, and institutional accreditation.',
            'Obtaining official transcripts and documents, which must be professionally translated and verified.',
            'Analyzing foreign qualifications in relation to the standards of the target country, considering content, duration, and program level.',
            'Consulting international databases, government publications, and scholarly articles on educational systems and equivalency standards.',
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="checklist-item">
              <span class="check-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" width="18" height="18">
                  <circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9" fill="var(--clr-primary-light)" stroke="var(--clr-primary)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
                  <path d="M6 10l3 3 5-6" stroke="var(--clr-primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span class="check-text">{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── EXPERT ASSESSMENT ── -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container expert-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>Expert Assessment</h2>
        <p class="method-italic" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
          This approach entails seeking input from experts in the relevant field who can
          evaluate the equivalency of foreign qualifications b
        </p>
        <ul class="checklist" style="margin-top:1rem;">
          {[
            'Evaluating the curriculum and learning outcomes of the foreign program in comparison to the standards of the target country.',
            'Reviewing transcripts, diplomas, and other documentation to validate qualifications and achievements.',
            "Comparing the applicant's skills and knowledge to the expected level of a graduate from a similar program in the target country.",
          ].map(item => (
            <li class="checklist-item">
              <span class="check-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" width="18" height="18">
                  <circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9" fill="var(--clr-primary-light)" stroke="var(--clr-primary)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
                  <path d="M6 10l3 3 5-6" stroke="var(--clr-primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span class="check-text">{item}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <img src="/LCA-Analysis-FOR-H-1B-RFE/LCA-Analysis-Img.jpg" alt="Expert Assessment" class="expert-img" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── GUIDING VALUES ── -->
  <section class="section-pad" style="background:var(--clr-bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cv-header">
        <div class="cv-header-left">
          <span class="eyebrow">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" width="10" height="10" aria-hidden="true" style="display:inline-block;vertical-align:middle;margin-right:4px;">
              <circle cx="7" cy="7" r="6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
            </svg>
            Methodology
          </span>
          <p style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.7;">
            Integrity, innovation, excellence—
            our core values shape our commitment to success.
          </p>
        </div>
        <h2 class="cv-heading">True Evaluators' Guiding Values in a Decade of Words.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="method-cards">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Data Collection',
            items: [
              "Gather comprehensive information about the applicant, their educational history, and the purpose of the evaluation through the application form.",
              "Collect and verify transcripts, diplomas, course descriptions, and other relevant documents.",
              "Request additional materials, such as letters of recommendation, CV/resume, to support the application.",
            ],
          },
          {
            title: 'Data Analysis',
            items: [
              "Thoroughly analyze documents, including transcripts and course descriptions, to understand the content and level of the applicant's education.",
              "Compare the foreign education system with the target country's system, assessing similarities and differences in credit systems, grading scales, and accreditation standards.",
              "Evaluate the applicant's overall academic performance, considering grades, course selection, and any additional achievements or experiences.",
            ],
          },
          {
            title: 'Evaluation and Reporting',
            items: [
              "Determine the equivalency level based on the analysis of the applicant's foreign qualification in the context of the target country's education system.",
              "Prepare a comprehensive evaluation report, clearly outlining the applicant's qualifications, the employed research methodology, the rationale for the equivalency determination, and any recommendations.",
            ],
          },
        ].map(card => (
          <div class="method-card">
            <h3>{card.title}</h3>
            <ul class="checklist" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
              {card.items.map(item => (
                <li class="checklist-item">
                  <span class="check-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                    <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" width="18" height="18">
                      <circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9" fill="var(--clr-primary-light)" stroke="var(--clr-primary)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
                      <path d="M6 10l3 3 5-6" stroke="var(--clr-primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                    </svg>
                  </span>
                  <span class="check-text">{item}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Conclusion paragraph -->
      <p class="conclusion-text">
        A meticulous research method and methodology are imperative for ensuring the accuracy and reliability of academic evaluations for foreign equivalency.
        Integrating a comparative approach with expert assessment enhances the evaluation process. Leveraging online databases, translation services, reference
        materials, and expert networks further contributes to a robust evaluation process. By implementing these methods and tools, academic institutions and
        licensing authorities can make informed decisions regarding the equivalency of foreign qualifications, ensuring fairness and transparency for international applicants.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
.inner-hero { background:var(--clr-bg-cream); padding-block:clamp(3rem,6vw,5rem); }
.inner-hero h1 { color:var(--clr-primary); font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3rem); }

.dual-imgs { display:grid; grid-template-columns:3fr 2fr; gap:1rem; }
@media (max-width:640px) { .dual-imgs { grid-template-columns:1fr; } }
.dual-img-main { height:clamp(320px,40vw,520px); border-radius:var(--radius-lg); width:100%; object-fit:cover; display:block; }
.dual-img-side { height:clamp(320px,40vw,520px); border-radius:var(--radius-lg); width:100%; object-fit:cover; display:block; }

.intro-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:2.5rem; align-items:start; }
@media (min-width:768px) { .intro-grid { grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; } }
.intro-label { font-weight:600; font-size:0.9rem; }

.comp-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:2.5rem; align-items:center; }
@media (min-width:768px) { .comp-grid { grid-template-columns:1fr 1.4fr; } }
.comp-img { width:100%; aspect-ratio:4/3; border-radius:var(--radius-lg); object-fit:cover; display:block; }

.expert-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:2.5rem; align-items:center; }
@media (min-width:768px) { .expert-grid { grid-template-columns:1.4fr 1fr; } }
.expert-img { width:100%; aspect-ratio:4/3; border-radius:var(--radius-lg); object-fit:cover; display:block; }

.method-italic { font-style:italic; color:var(--clr-primary); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.65; }

.checklist { list-style:none; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.75rem; }
.checklist-item { display:flex; gap:0.65rem; align-items:flex-start; }
.check-icon { flex-shrink:0; margin-top:2px; }
.check-text { font-size:0.86rem; color:var(--clr-primary); line-height:1.55; }

.cv-header { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:1.5rem; align-items:end; margin-bottom:2.5rem; }
@media (min-width:768px) { .cv-header { grid-template-columns:240px 1fr; } }
.cv-heading { font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,2.6rem); }

.method-cards { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:1.25rem; }
@media (min-width:640px)  { .method-cards { grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr); } }
@media (min-width:1024px) { .method-cards { grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); } }
.method-card {
  background:var(--clr-white); border:1px solid var(--clr-border);
  border-radius:var(--radius-lg); padding:1.75rem;
}
.method-card h3 { font-size:1rem; margin-bottom:0.25rem; }

.conclusion-text { margin-top:2.5rem; font-size:0.88rem; line-height:1.75; }
</style>
